    "course_description" : "Computer graphics, the Internet, mobile media players, social networking (e.g. blogs or YouTube), high-quality consumer cameras, and inexpensive post-production software. These innovations have transformed the way movies are made and consumed. Old models of production have been transformed. New genres and styles have been born. Moviesif that term is still applicableare consumed in new and more varied ways than ever before. Production and consumption have even begun to blur as the tools for making, remixing, and distributing media are democratized. This course will attempt to take account of these changes, looking at a wide variety of films and media from computer animation to documentary films to video games to made-for-internet media. We will also look at the changing landscape of film distribution and exhibition from iTunes and the iPod to YouTube to new 3-D formats. Readings will be drawn from an interdisciplinary range of approaches to understanding new media.",
