    "course_description" : "The seminar will be concerned with witnessing as a discursive, historical and ethical practice and its relation to media, old and new. Witnessing will be cast as a crucial concept for contemporary ethically-informed discussions in media and communication. Among the issues to be discussed: witnessing and responsibility according to Levinas; the trauma testimony discourse; media and trauma: the case of the Eichmann trial; testimony and the Video Archive for Holocaust Testimonies; witnessing via the media witnessing discourse; distant suffering. Readings will include texts by Emmanuel Levinas, Dori Laub and Shoshana Felman, Giorgio Agamben, Geoffrey Hartman, Jeffery Alexander, Luc Boltanski, John Ellis, John Durham Peters, as well as my own work.",
