    "course_description" : "This course examines\"collective memory\" through theoretical, historical and critical lenses. Signaling a concern with how, what, why and for whom collectives remember this phenomenon is closely tied to issues of identities, media technologies, politics and conflict, as well as imaginaries of the future. Memory by its very nature is mediated, and collective memory is even moreso, given the centrality of communications technologies in structuring imagined communities. Examining the technologies, strategies and politics of collective memory here is to go beyond the subject and foster an understanding of the intricacies and intersections of culture, communication and critical theory.",
